eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu has more. #Dstv403 JOHANNESBURG - Clean-up operations at SABC radio park in Johannesburg continue on Thursday. This after a diesel spill flooded the building on Wednesday. Thousands of litres oozed out of a back-up generator. WATCH: SABC offices evacuated after diesel leak Some national radio stations, including Radio 2000 and Metro FM, were left on autopilot for several hours. The public broadcaster has blamed old infrastructure. WATCH: SABC fires Chris Maroleng Robert Mulaudzi, Johannesburg emergency services spokesperson, said one of the standby generators leaked as a result of wear and tear due to age. Mulaudzi stated the 15th floor was completely flooded and the whole building was affected by the smell.